headline: How The Phillips 66 (PSX) Story Is Shifting With Midstream Growth And Valuation Debates
summary: Phillips 66’s fair value estimate has been nudged from US$155.70 to US$157.55, a modest uplift of about US$1.85 per share that puts fresh attention on where the current price sits versus updated models. That adjustment comes as analysts refresh their Q4 work and debate how much midstream growth and sector sentiment are already reflected in existing targets.
